ellar mass of M_* ~ 4x10^11 h^{-2} M_sun. Our study\nprovides an example of massive, dusty star-forming galaxies contributing to the\nGRB host galaxy population, supporting the notion that long-duration GRBs trace\nthe bulk of cosmic star formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Oct 2010 20:00:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 Oct 2010 15:53:09 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 10 Dec 2010 22:10:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-20"}
